WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:08.000
Simon's simples at the station is going on a train.

00:08.000 --> 00:12.000
There are policemen at the station.

00:12.000 --> 00:16.000
There are policemen on the trains.

00:16.000 --> 00:20.000
They're all working very hard.

00:20.000 --> 00:23.000
Why are the police here?

00:23.000 --> 00:25.000
Simon asks a man.

00:25.000 --> 00:29.000
Look, the man says.

00:29.000 --> 00:33.000
Simon looks at the man's newspaper.

00:33.000 --> 00:37.000
Do you know this man? He reads.

00:37.000 --> 00:44.000
He's a spy. Find him. Stop him. Catch him.

00:44.000 --> 00:48.000
Simon looks at the people in the station.

00:48.000 --> 00:54.000
He can see students in jeans and men in suits.

00:54.000 --> 00:58.000
He can see families and children.

00:58.000 --> 01:02.000
He can't see any spies.

01:02.000 --> 01:09.000
Simon's train goes at 11, and it's 1057 now.

01:09.000 --> 01:12.000
Simon runs to the train.

01:12.000 --> 01:16.000
There's an old woman with an umbrella near Simon.

01:16.000 --> 01:19.000
She's walking very fast.

01:19.000 --> 01:22.000
Simon doesn't see her.

01:22.000 --> 01:24.000
He doesn't see her bag.

01:24.000 --> 01:28.000
The old woman's bag hits Simon's foot.

01:28.000 --> 01:31.000
Simon falls.

01:31.000 --> 01:33.000
His bag opens.

01:33.000 --> 01:37.000
His things fall to the ground.

01:37.000 --> 01:40.000
The old woman's bag is open too.

01:40.000 --> 01:43.000
A letter falls out.

01:43.000 --> 01:47.000
Simon puts his things into his bag.

01:47.000 --> 01:51.000
The old woman's letter is with Simon's things.

01:51.000 --> 01:54.000
Simon doesn't see it.

01:54.000 --> 01:58.000
He puts the old woman's letter in his bag.

01:58.000 --> 02:02.000
He closes his bag and runs to the train.

02:02.000 --> 02:05.000
Simon sits down in the train.

02:05.000 --> 02:09.000
There's a beautiful girl beside him.

02:09.000 --> 02:12.000
Hello, Simon says.

02:12.000 --> 02:15.000
Hello, the girl says.

02:15.000 --> 02:19.000
The old woman's on the train too.

02:19.000 --> 02:23.000
She's looking at Simon's bag.

02:23.000 --> 02:26.000
She wants her letter.

02:26.000 --> 02:29.000
There are policemen on the train.

02:29.000 --> 02:32.000
They can't find the spy.

02:32.000 --> 02:36.000
The old woman sees the policeman.

02:36.000 --> 02:40.000
She turns and walks quickly down the train.

02:40.000 --> 02:43.000
Simon likes the girl.

02:43.000 --> 02:46.000
She likes him.

02:46.000 --> 02:49.000
There's a restaurant on the train.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.000
Simon says.

02:51.000 --> 02:54.000
Do you want a cup of coffee?

02:54.000 --> 02:56.000
Yes, please.

02:56.000 --> 02:57.000
The girl says.

02:57.000 --> 02:59.000
Okay, wait here.

02:59.000 --> 03:03.000
Simon says.

03:03.000 --> 03:07.000
Simon takes his bag and goes to the restaurant.

03:07.000 --> 03:10.000
The old woman's waiting for him.

03:10.000 --> 03:13.000
Simon doesn't see her.

03:13.000 --> 03:16.000
The train's going fast.

03:16.000 --> 03:19.000
Simon falls.

03:19.000 --> 03:22.000
The old woman falls too.

03:22.000 --> 03:25.000
She sits down on the floor.

03:25.000 --> 03:29.000
Oh, I'm sorry, Simon says.

03:29.000 --> 03:32.000
He helps the old woman.

03:32.000 --> 03:36.000
Simon sees the old woman's shoes.

03:36.000 --> 03:41.000
He looks at her shoes and he looks at her face.

03:41.000 --> 03:46.000
They're not women's shoes, Simon thinks.

03:46.000 --> 03:51.000
Simon buys the coffee and goes back to the girl.

03:51.000 --> 03:54.000
The train stops.

03:54.000 --> 03:58.000
Simon and the girl are going on a boat now.

03:58.000 --> 04:02.000
They walk from the train to the boat.

04:02.000 --> 04:05.000
There are policemen here too.

04:05.000 --> 04:08.000
What do they want?

04:09.000 --> 04:11.000
What do they want?

04:11.000 --> 04:13.000
The girl asks.

04:13.000 --> 04:15.000
There's a spy.

04:15.000 --> 04:17.000
Simon says.

04:17.000 --> 04:18.000
A spy?

04:18.000 --> 04:20.000
The girl says.

04:20.000 --> 04:23.000
I can't see any spies.

04:23.000 --> 04:26.000
Simon looks too.

04:26.000 --> 04:29.000
He sees families and students.

04:29.000 --> 04:31.000
He sees the old woman.

04:31.000 --> 04:33.000
No.

04:33.000 --> 04:35.000
Simon says.

04:35.000 --> 04:39.000
I can't see any spies.

04:39.000 --> 04:42.000
It's a beautiful day.

04:42.000 --> 04:46.000
The sun's shining and the water's blue.

04:46.000 --> 04:51.000
Simon and the girl sit near the water and wait.

04:51.000 --> 04:54.000
The boat's coming.

04:54.000 --> 04:56.000
What's your name?

04:56.000 --> 04:58.000
Simon asks.

04:58.000 --> 04:59.000
Samantha.

04:59.000 --> 05:01.000
The girl says.

05:01.000 --> 05:04.000
Oh, Simon says.

05:04.000 --> 05:06.000
My name's Simon.

05:06.000 --> 05:09.000
Simon and Samantha.

05:09.000 --> 05:12.000
That's nice.

05:12.000 --> 05:15.000
Simon and Samantha are talking.

05:15.000 --> 05:18.000
They don't see the old woman.

05:18.000 --> 05:22.000
They don't see her umbrella.

05:22.000 --> 05:24.000
Look out!

05:24.000 --> 05:26.000
A man shouts.

05:26.000 --> 05:28.000
There's a lorry!

05:28.000 --> 05:32.000
Simon and Samantha look.

05:32.000 --> 05:36.000
A lorry is coming down the road very fast.

05:36.000 --> 05:38.000
They jump back.

05:42.000 --> 05:45.000
The old woman jumps back too.

05:45.000 --> 05:49.000
Simon sees the trousers.

05:49.000 --> 05:52.000
They're not women's trousers.

05:52.000 --> 05:54.000
Simon thinks.

05:54.000 --> 05:55.000
Come on, Simon.

05:55.000 --> 05:57.000
The boat's here.

05:57.000 --> 05:59.000
Samantha says.

05:59.000 --> 06:03.000
Simon and Samantha get on the boat.

06:03.000 --> 06:08.000
Simon opens his bag and takes his lunch out.

06:08.000 --> 06:14.000
He takes the old woman's letter out too, but he doesn't see it.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.000
Do you want a sandwich?

06:16.000 --> 06:18.000
Simon asks Samantha.

06:18.000 --> 06:20.000
Yes, please.

06:20.000 --> 06:22.000
Samantha says.

06:22.000 --> 06:26.000
She takes her lunch out of her bag.

06:26.000 --> 06:28.000
Do you want an apple?

06:28.000 --> 06:30.000
She says.

06:30.000 --> 06:32.000
The old woman's behind them.

06:32.000 --> 06:36.000
Simon and Samantha don't see her.

06:36.000 --> 06:39.000
They don't see her hand.

06:39.000 --> 06:42.000
The boat's going fast now.

06:42.000 --> 06:45.000
The wind's strong.

06:45.000 --> 06:48.000
Samantha's hair goes in her eyes.

06:48.000 --> 06:52.000
The wind takes the old woman's letter.

06:52.000 --> 06:55.000
The letter flies along the boat.

06:55.000 --> 06:57.000
What's that paper?

06:57.000 --> 06:59.000
Samantha says.

06:59.000 --> 07:01.000
Is it your boat, ticket?

07:01.000 --> 07:03.000
I don't know.

07:03.000 --> 07:05.000
Simon says.

07:05.000 --> 07:07.000
Simon runs.

07:07.000 --> 07:09.000
He wants his ticket.

07:09.000 --> 07:11.000
The old woman runs too.

07:11.000 --> 07:14.000
She wants her letter.

07:14.000 --> 07:17.000
Simon and the old woman run fast.

07:17.000 --> 07:20.000
They're near the paper now.

07:21.000 --> 07:24.000
What's that?

07:24.000 --> 07:26.000
It's a dog.

07:26.000 --> 07:28.000
He's running very fast.

07:28.000 --> 07:33.000
He runs to the paper and catches it in his mouth.

07:33.000 --> 07:35.000
My ticket.

07:35.000 --> 07:37.000
Simon says.

07:37.000 --> 07:39.000
My letter.

07:39.000 --> 07:41.000
The old woman says.

07:41.000 --> 07:44.000
The dog runs along the boat.

07:44.000 --> 07:46.000
Catch the dog.

07:46.000 --> 07:48.000
Simon says.

07:48.000 --> 07:50.000
Stop him!

07:50.000 --> 07:52.000
Says the old woman.

07:52.000 --> 07:54.000
The dog's happy.

07:54.000 --> 07:56.000
He can run fast.

07:56.000 --> 08:00.000
He's playing a game with Simon and the old woman.

08:00.000 --> 08:03.000
He doesn't see Samantha.

08:03.000 --> 08:06.000
Samantha jumps up and catches him.

08:06.000 --> 08:08.000
I've got him, Simon.

08:08.000 --> 08:10.000
Samantha says.

08:10.000 --> 08:14.000
Simon and the old woman run to Samantha.

08:14.000 --> 08:17.000
The paper's in the dog's mouth.

08:17.000 --> 08:19.000
Simon looks at it.

08:19.000 --> 08:21.000
That's not my ticket.

08:21.000 --> 08:22.000
He says.

08:22.000 --> 08:23.000
No.

08:23.000 --> 08:25.000
The old woman says.

08:25.000 --> 08:27.000
It's my letter.

08:27.000 --> 08:30.000
The dog likes Simon and Samantha.

08:30.000 --> 08:33.000
But he doesn't like the old woman.

08:33.000 --> 08:37.000
He takes her coat in his mouth and pulls it.

08:37.000 --> 08:40.000
The coat falls to the ground.

08:40.000 --> 08:43.000
The wind takes the old woman's hat.

08:43.000 --> 08:45.000
It falls into the water.

08:45.000 --> 08:48.000
The hair falls with the hat.

08:48.000 --> 08:52.000
Simon and Samantha look at the old woman.

08:52.000 --> 08:54.000
It's not an old woman.

08:54.000 --> 08:56.000
It's a man.

08:56.000 --> 08:58.000
The spy.

08:58.000 --> 09:00.000
Simon says.

09:00.000 --> 09:03.000
Police, come here.

09:03.000 --> 09:08.000
The police are very happy.

09:08.000 --> 09:11.000
Thank you, Simon.

09:11.000 --> 09:13.000
They say.

09:13.000 --> 09:16.000
Now we have the spy.

09:16.000 --> 09:19.000
But the spy has a letter.

09:19.000 --> 09:23.000
The letter has names and addresses on it.

09:23.000 --> 09:27.000
We want the letter, but we can't find it.

09:27.000 --> 09:29.000
Where is it?

09:29.000 --> 09:31.000
Do you know?

09:31.000 --> 09:34.000
Simon looks at the dog.

09:34.000 --> 09:37.000
The dog looks at Simon.

09:37.000 --> 09:39.000
There's the letter.

09:39.000 --> 09:41.000
Simon says.

09:41.000 --> 09:42.000
Where?

09:42.000 --> 09:44.000
Says the policeman.

09:44.000 --> 09:49.000
It's in the dog, Simon says.

